OL,5,Cbosses
OL,7,F"No one wants to see the cost of an
OL,8,Faverage pint increase by a further 21p
OL,9,Fand break the #5 average pint barrier
OL,10,Fthat will be required for pubs to
OL,11,Fmaintain their punishingly slim profit
OL,12,Fmargins.
OL,14,F"It is more urgent than ever that
OL,15,FGovernment looks at ways to cap or
OL,16,Freduce the costs of doing business so
OL,17,Fwe can keep pubs open, preserve their
OL,18,Fcommunity value, and make sure the
OL,19,Fprice of a pint remains affordable for
OL,20,Fall."
